<font color="#FF0000">A MATTER OF TRUST</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 16 12:53:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
It is not wrong not to trust others.  It is important to remember those words, &quot;To thine own self be true&quot;.  <br><br>
Trust is not given lightly.  I too struggle with trusting myself.  Not trusting can be a paralyzing mechanism.  Better to do nothing than to do the wrong thing.  A problem we didn't have in the war.  We reacted off instinct because of the immediate need to act.  It wasn't a matter of trust it was a matter of needing a resolution.  We trusted our Bros. because we knew we could not possess the entire solution.  We could not survive without each other.<br><br>
Our insight and perception of the reality quickly exposed that which could not be trusted.  If you remember the other Bros. would feel the same way.  Trust was that element you used when you didn't have a solution and you found yourself immediately looking to that someone for help.  When you were beyond the bounds of your brother's control, you immediately looked to God.  Faith in the fact that we needed something to hold on to.  We can not survive when we are alone.  It is this, alone which is created by our inability to trust.<br><br>
Everyone does not deserve trust and no guilt should be felt.  We are human and must always struggle with our frailties.<br><br>
We are all capable of evil and good.  It is merely the balance that brings peace.  There are those who seek our trust because they wish to exercise the evil that is within them.  Trust is not given to those that would do us harm.  No guilt necessary.<br><br>
We have been disappointed so many times we become polarized in our reactions to life.  We expect the rest of society to meet our standards.  As we know this is unreasonable.  Many do not have our values.  The civilian is a me person.  You can never trust a me person; they will always disappoint you.<br><br>
Struggle with the reality we have been given, but remember that if you do not learn to trust yourself it will be difficult if not impossible to trust others.<br><br>
We trust you Bro. So just maybe you have missed an important point in your self-evaluation.<br><br>
Trust those who have honor and integrity.  Somehow you will know.  You have already trusted such men.<br><br>
Remember that just because you survived don't mean you broke the trust your brothers who were less fortunate gave you.  You did your best for the group and not just for the self.<br><br>
You are my Brother of Choice and to you I give my trust.  Men have put their lives in your hands, what more could you ask?<br>

